mp3player.desktopaudio

Class AudioEngine

  • java.lang.Object
    • mp3player.desktopaudio.AudioEngine

  • public abstract class AudioEngine
extends java.lang.Object
    AudioEngine represents a backend interface for playing audio. Only one instance of AudioEngine is needed by an application to use the library.
    Author:
    Philipp Holl

    • Method Detail

      • newPlayer

        public abstract Player newPlayer(MediaFile media)
        Creates a new player for the given media. The player is not prepared and no data will be read during the creation process.

        If a player for this media already exists, they might share a single buffer, depending on the implementation.

        Parameters:
        media - the player's MediaFile object
        Returns:
        a new player for the given media

        Throws:
